title: RJHS Lady Whirlwinds take second at LH Invite
text: RJHS Lady Whirlwinds take second at LH Invite by Courier sports staff The Courier Your Messenger For The River Valley 02:09 PM, Wednesday, October 21 2015 | 56 views | 0 | 0 | | LAKE HAMILTON â€” The Russellville Cyclones and Lady Cyclones cross country teams recently competed in the Lake Hamilton Invitational.The Lady Whirlwinds placed second with 63 points and wer eled by Charissa Helms with her 10th place finish in 13:55.33. Emily Austin placed 14th in 14:04.18.Other top finishers for the Lady Whirlwinds were Angel Henning (14:08.04), Selena Vazquez (14:14.19), Lauren Skartvedt (14:13.81) and Diana Nava (14:33.92).The Whirlwinds finished sixth with a team score of 206. They were led by Hunter Maestas (12:50.95), Brandon Preston (12:52.11), Paul Weatherford (13:15.57) and Cole Whittle (13:16.34).The Lady Cyclones placed ninth with a team score of 270. They were led by Astrid Christianson in 20:51.56, Kenya McDaniel (21:58.32), Kalley Williams (22:26.33) and Madelyn Hubbard (22:35.26).The Cyclones were led by Austin Lesser in 18:17.57 and Luis Lobato in 18:46.55. Andy Ward finished in 19:20.99 and Kevin Almazam in 19:31.47.
